3 SENATE BILL NO. 1430 By: Jech
4
5
6 An Act relating to the Department of Mental Health
and Substance Abuse Services; amending 43A O.S. 2021,
7 Section 2-101, which relates to the Board of Mental
Health and Substance Abuse Services; modifying
8 appointing authority of the Commissioner of Mental
Health and Substance Abuse Services; conforming
9 language; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 43A O.S. 2021, Section 2-101, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 2-101. A. 1. There is hereby established in this
16 state a Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services.
17 2. This Department’s governing board shall be the Board of
18 Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services, and its chief executive
19 officer shall be the Commissioner of Mental Health and Substance
20 Abuse Services. The Commissioner shall be appointed by the Governor
21 with the advice and consent of the Senate and shall serve at the
22 pleasure of the Governor Board and may be removed or replaced
23 without cause. Compensation for the Commissioner shall be
24 determined by the Governor. The Commissioner may be removed from
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1430 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 offi ce by a two-thirds (2/3) vote of the members elected to and
2 constituting each chamber of the Legislature Board.
3 3. The Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services
4 shall exercise all functions of the state in relation to the
5 administration and operation of all state facilities for the care
6 and treatment of the mentally ill and drug- or alcohol-dependent
7 persons.
8 B. All references in the Oklahoma Statutes to the Department of
9 Mental Health or the Board of Mental Health shall be construed to
10 refer to the Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
11 Services or the Board of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services,
12 respectively.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
14 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
